A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Chapter 11 of Title 45 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 miscellaneous offenses concerning public officers and employees, so as to modify provisions
3 relating to public officials engaging in the bail bond business; to provide for related matters;
4 to provide an effective date; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
6 SECTION 1.
7 Chapter 11 of Title 45 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to miscellaneous
8 offenses concerning public officers and employees, is amended by revising Code
9 Section 45-11-8, relating to engaging in bail bond business, as follows:
10 "45-11-8.
11 (a)(1) It shall be unlawful for any elected official, officer of the court, law enforcement
12 officer, or attorney in this state to engage either directly or indirectly in the bail bond
13 business. For purposes of this Code section paragraph, the term 'elected official' shall not
14 include a person who is elected to as a member of the local school board or the governing
15 authority of a county, municipal corporation, or consolidated government.
