16 (2) It shall be unlawful for any person who is a member of the governing authority of a
17 county, municipal corporation, or consolidated government to engage either directly or
18 indirectly in the bail bond business within the jurisdiction of the county, municipal
19 corporation, or consolidated government where such person holds office.
20 (b) Any person who violates this Code section shall be guilty of a misdemeanor."
21 SECTION 2.
22 This Act shall become effective upon its approval by the Governor or upon its becoming law
23 without such approval.
24 SECTION 3.
25 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
